# OneWorld Launch-Grade Package

This package upgrades the prior scaffold into a launch-ready baseline with CEO-only access locked to Jessica Chekwube Achebe.

## Included
- FastAPI backend with:
  - PostgreSQL
  - Alembic migrations
  - Redis-backed rate limiting
  - JWT auth
  - email verification and password reset
  - Stripe checkout portal scaffolding
  - Sentry initialization
  - analytics event ingestion
- Expo React Native frontend with:
  - onboarding
  - auth context
  - forgot/reset password
  - upgrade screen
  - settings screen
- Docker Compose for local full-stack development

## Quick start

### 1) Backend env
```bash
cd backend
cp .env.example .env
```

### 2) Start services
From the project root:
```bash
docker compose up --build
```

Backend API:
- http://localhost:8000
- docs at http://localhost:8000/docs

### 3) Frontend env
```bash
cd frontend
cp .env.example .env
npm install
npm start
```

Set `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` to your machine IP if you test on a physical device.

## Production wiring checklist
- Set real secrets in `backend/.env`
- Set `APP_BASE_URL`, `FRONTEND_URL`, `SMTP_*`, `STRIPE_*`, `SENTRY_DSN`
- Run Alembic migrations:
```bash
docker compose exec backend alembic upgrade head
```
- Use managed Postgres and Redis in production
- Configure HTTPS and a real domain
- Lock down CORS origins
- Replace the demo analytics store with a warehouse or product analytics tool

## Notes
- Email sending is fully wired through SMTP, but without real SMTP credentials messages will fail.
- Stripe endpoints are wired for real keys, but you still need to configure products and webhook secrets.
- Sentry is initialized only when `SENTRY_DSN` is present.


## Scale upgrade added in this package
- offline chat history and queued scan storage
- scan screen using Expo Camera and image import
- AI routing + Redis cache for cost control
- growth scripts and offline architecture docs in `/docs`

## New endpoints
- `POST /utility/chat`
- `POST /utility/scan`
- `POST /utility/translate`
- `POST /utility/budget`

## Frontend install note
After pulling this version, run `npx expo install expo-camera expo-file-system expo-image-picker` so the native packages match your Expo SDK.


## Owner-only access
- Public registration is disabled.
- On startup, the backend seeds exactly one owner account using `OWNER_EMAIL`, `OWNER_PASSWORD`, and `OWNER_FULL_NAME`.
- This build defaults `OWNER_FULL_NAME` to `Jessica Chekwube Achebe`.
- Only the owner account can log in to this deployment.


